Contents:
* LICENSE   - license for the OshaJava distribution
* README    - this file
* build.xml - ant build file
* libs      - third party libs used by OshaJava, renamed for
  	   		  instrumentation reentrancy
* src       - the OshaJava source
* todo      - to-do lists

Required:
* Java 1.6 or higher
* ant
* sh-compatible shell
 
Build:
1. Run ant in the top-level directory.  
2. Source setup.sh in any shell where you want to use oshajava.  It
   sets some environment variables and puts a few utilities on your
   path.

See http://bitbucket.org/bpw/oshajava for more documentation.